<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="332" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">662.116/212</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German Ministry for
                                        Foreign Affairs</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                        Embassy in Germany</gloss></hi><note n="17" xml:id="d332fn17">Copy transmitted to the Department by the
                                    Chargé in Germany in his despatch No. 839, May 16; received May
                                    25.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. W 2770</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Note Verbale</hi></p>
                            <p>The Foreign Office has the honor to state to the Embassy of the
                                United States of America—in reply to the latter’s <hi rend="italic">note verbale</hi> of April 11, No. 215—the following:</p>
                            <pb facs="0524" n="424" xml:id="pg_424"/>
                            <p>The structure of customs contingents in commercial treaty agreements
                                with other states takes into account primarily the interests of the
                                state with which the customs contingent is agreed upon by treaty. In
                                this connection, the equivalent offered by this state for the
                                granting of the customs contingent is of course of importance.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-09">May
                                        9, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>